events.name: Building a Chatbot with Dialogflow
events.description:
BUILDING A CHATBOT WITH DIALOGFLOW

This is a workshop where you will be building a chatbot using Dialogflow. Dialogflow is a developer tool released by Google for developers to create apps for the Google Assistant. It would then run on mobile phones and smart home devices such as Google Home and Google Home Hub) .

Prerequisites:
No programming experience is required. Participants will be split into two groups: those who know Javascript and those who don’t. Please state which group you would like to join in the RSVP form (bit.ly/gdgbrunei-rsvp) The first group may be doing a little programming, depending on time, and the second group will not be coding at all. (But most of the content will be the same).

Dialogflow is a managed cloud service: everything is online. You only need a gmail account.

RSVP form: bit.ly/gdgbrunei-rsvp
Infosheet: bit.ly/gdgbrunei-info

events.name: Casual Coding + Solution Sprint
events.description:
Date: 20th September 2019
Time: 7pm-9:30pm
Location: iCentre Ground Floor

A casual coding space where you can bring your projects and meet other developers.
We will also run a Solution Sprint mini game at the same time.

Solution Sprint (No RSVP needed, starts promptly at 7):

You will be given a Challenge on the day. Team up and work with other developers to build a prototype in 2 hrs.

This is meant to be a fun exercise: at the end of the day whatever you build will be yours. The goal is to flex your programming muscles and get them ready for DevFest. Bring your laptops!

The theme this week is: Dialogflow
Dialagflow is a Google product used to build conversational chatbots. You can integrate the chatbot into a variety of platforms, including Google Assistant, Amazon Alexa, Slack, Whatsapp, Facebook Messenger and more.

The Challenge will be released at 7pm sharp.

Solution Sprint Prerequisites:
- It is preferred if you know Dialogflow or have attended the previous event: Building a Chatbot with Dialogflow. Or you can come on the day and learn from the internet.
- Participants will be left to their own devices with minimal supervision: be prepared to use Google!
- Bring a laptop

See you there!

events.name: Road to DevFest: Create a Realtime Web App with Firebase’s Cloud Firestore
events.description:
This is a free workshop where you will be using Firebase’s Cloud Firestore to explore its realtime update capabilities.

Cloud Firestore is a flexible, scalable database for mobile, web, and server development from Firebase and Google Cloud Platform. It keeps your data in sync across client apps through realtime listeners and offers offline support for mobile and web so you can build responsive apps that work regardless of network latency or Internet connectivity.

For this workshop we will be using Javascript, and you will be introduced to Firestore’s Node.js client library. Cloud Firestore’s client libraries are available in C#, Go, Java, Kotlin, Node.js, Objective-C, PHP, Python, Ruby, Swift.

By the end of the workshop you will have a working web app connected to the Firestore database, and be able to see the realtime updates to the web app.

Date: Thursday 3rd October 2019
Time: 7pm - 9:30pm
Location: REGUS 8th Floor PGGMB, Kianggeh Rd, Bandar Seri Begawan BS8111

Prerequisites
This event is tailored for programmers – but everyone is very much welcome to join! There will be two levels:
• Beginner – People who do not know Javascript/Typescript/NodeJS. Most of the code will be given to you
• Intermediate – those who have basic understanding of JavaScript/Typescript/NodeJS

Please state which group you would like to join in the RSVP form (bit.ly/gdgbrunei-rsvp)

To RSVP:
1. Fill in the form: bit.ly/gdgbrunei-rsvp
2. Click "Going" on the Meetup event

Event Details: bit.ly/gdgbrunei-info
Our calendar: bit.ly/gdgbrunei-calendar

Please bring your laptop with the following installed!
1. Visual Studio Code: https://code.visualstudio.com/download
2. npm: https://nodejs.org/en/
3. git: https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/install-git
4. Firebase CLI: (just run "npm install -g firebase-tools" in your Terminal(Linux/Mac) or Windows Command Prompt)

events.name: Road to DevFest : Creating a Smart Home Alarm with Raspberry Pi & Cloud Pub/Sub
events.description:
This is a free workshop where you will be building a miniature home alarm system and connecting it to the cloud with Raspberry Pi and Google Cloud Pub/Sub.

Raspberry Pi is a card sized computer commonly used in IoT projects. It is often used as a tool to teach programming.

Google Cloud Pub/Sub is a fully-managed real-time messaging service that allows you to send and receive messages between independent applications. It is part of Google Cloud Platform.

This workshop will be hands-on: you will be building a simplified home alarm circuit, and then programming the Raspberry Pi to interact with the circuit. You will then connect it to the Cloud with Cloud Pub/Sub, turning the Raspberry Pi into an IoT device. This allows you to receive telemetry events from the Raspberry Pi and to push configurations.

Date: Thursday, 31st October 2019
Time: 7:00pm to 9:30pm
Location: To be confirmed via whatsapp message

Prerequisites:
No programming experience is required. Python will be used for the event but most of the code will be provided to you.

Please bring:
Your laptop with the following installed:
-Python3
-Laptop charger
-Your enthusiasm!

To sign up:
You MUST fill in the RSVP form (bit.ly/gdgbrunei-rsvp)
Please also click “You’re going” on Meetup (bit.ly/gdgbrunei-meetup)

Spaces are limited, please sign up via the RSVP form. The location of the event will be sent to you if you are successful.
